
[1]epispastic

   EPISPAS'TIC, a. [Gr. to draw.] In medicine, drawing; attracting the
   humors to the skin; exciting action in the skin; blistering.

   EPISPAS'TIC, n. A topical remedy, applied to the external part of the
   body, for the purpose of drawing the humors to the part, or exciting
   action in the skin; a blister.
